Drain peaches reserving 1 cup syrup into small saucepan; set peaches aside. Add cornstarch and cinnamon to syrup; stir to dissolve cornstarch. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and translucent. Moisten banana with lemon juice to prevent browning. Combine banana, peaches and grapes with syrup mixture. Place ham slices over waffles. Top with fruit and syrup mixture.